# Trivy ignore rules
#
# Format: one rule per line. `<id>` ignores globally; `<id>:<path>` scopes
# the suppression to a single file.
#
# Each entry should explain WHY the finding is acceptable in this codebase.
# Adding to this file means we're choosing not to fix; new Dockerfiles still
# get scanned because suppressions are file-scoped, not blanket.

# DS-0002 — "Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile"
#
# These are local-only utility containers running on Matt's PC behind a
# Tailscale tunnel — no internet exposure, no multi-tenant surface, no
# attacker-reachable network from inside the docker-compose network.
# A container-escape from any of them would land on the host where the
# operator already has root. The "run as non-root" hardening doesn't
# move the needle for this threat model.
#
# - auto-embed: pgvector worker, internal-only, scripted in shell
# - gpu-exporter: NVIDIA SMI scraper, needs device access to /dev/nvidia*
# - voice-bot: local TTS / audio pipeline, needs ALSA/audio device access
#
# Re-evaluate if any of these grow inbound network exposure.
DS-0002:scripts/Dockerfile.auto-embed
DS-0002:scripts/Dockerfile.gpu-exporter
DS-0002:scripts/Dockerfile.voice-bot
